Apostle Chibuzo Chinyere of the popular Omega Power Ministry, OPM, has offered to relocate the parents and siblings of the murdered student of Shehu Shagari College of Education, Sokoto State, Deborah Samuel to Port Harcourt. The man of God has also promised to enrol the siblings of the killed student in the church-owned school, free of cost Deborah was lynched and burnt to death by some Muslim youths on Thursday over an alleged act of blasphemy in a class WhatsApp group. Her parents had in an interview with DAILY POST on Sunday, said, Deborah’s siblings sacrificed their education for their murdered sister over the lack of finances to enrol all of them at the same time. She told DAILY POST that her seven children would not be able to access education ever again. However, the OPM philanthropist has now promised to take over Debora’s siblings’ education. The man of God in a statement currently trending on social media said he would relocate the family from Niger State to Port Harcourt the Rivers State capital. He said, “I just watched a video clip where the parents of Deborah Samuel said they will not be sending their children to school again. GOD FORBID. “Anyone with their contacts should inform them immediately that I Apostle Chibuzor Chinyere, the general overseas of OPM Church is relocating them to Port Harcourt. “They would be staying in one of the OPM’s free estates where they will never pay rent forever. ”All their children are given automatic scholarships in OPM Free schools. “I will get the father a job and I will also open a shop for the mother. Please get in touch with them immediately.
God bless you”.